          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Workforce Development Through Post-Graduation Scholarships Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude post-graduation scholarship grants from gross income in the same manner as scholarships are currently excluded. </p> <p>A &quot;post-graduation scholarship grant&quot; is a grant provided by a program that: (1) is established by certain tax-exempt organizations; (2) is designed to encourage individuals to serve in occupations of unmet needs or in areas of unmet needs; and (3) under which, in accordance with the conditions of a grant, the organization repays any portion of an education loan incurred by an individual to pay higher education expenses. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-07-24T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
